					Biographies





Name
Description




							Abiodun Fawunmi


					
							Mr. Abiodun Bamidele Fawunmi has served as Non-Executive Chairman of Computer Warehouse Group Plc since November 22, 2015. He served as Non-Executive Director of the Company until November 22, 2015. He is experienced in technology. In his career, he has led multi-cultural professional teams to high levels of effectiveness in a variety of competitive industries and fast-paced environments. Armed with technical and business qualifications, he has created an impressive track record of more than 35 years of hands-on experience in strategic planning, business unit development and resource management. He holds Post-graduate level degrees in Engineering, Computing and Business Administration from various African and European Universities. He also had short term training in Finance, Management of International Organizations and Developmental Economics from Ivy League Universities. He has played significant roles in multi-national organizations such as Shell, Unilever, PriceWaterhouseCoopers and Coca-Cola. Between 2004 and 2011, he was the Head of Infrastructure Services at the United Nations International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) in Vienna. He is currently the Chief Information Officer (CIO) at the United Nations International Criminal Tribunal for Rwanda (UNICTR). As co-founder of NEOPANORA (an international network of Energy professionals) he led a team that provided pro bono advisory services to National Governments on renewable energy. He relishes working with and supporting Nigerian Institutions of Higher learning as well as People living with HIV/AIDS (PLWHA). Abiodun is a Non-Executive Director of CWG and the Chairman of GENCOM. 




							James Agada


					
							Mr. James Agada has served as Chief Executive Officer, Executive Director of Computer Warehouse Group Plc since January 1, 2016. He served as Chief Technology Officer, Executive Director of the Company until January 1, 2016. He holds both a first class degree and a Masters Degree in Electronic Engineering, with specialization in Digital Systems, from the University of Nigeria, Nsukka. He also holds an MBA from Instituto de Estudios Superiores de la Empresa (IESE), Navara, Spain. James is an Executive Director of the Company and is highly regarded in the IT industry where he has spent over 20 years building a career in consulting, software development, implementation and support. He was pro tem president, Lagos Chapter of the Nigeria Computer Society, and was conferred with the Titans of Tech Merit Award in 2013, by Technology Africa. He is the Chief Technology Officer of the Company, and the Executive Director overseeing the Company's software division, ExpertEdge. James has the primary responsibility for the Company's research and development unit.




							Austin Okere


					
							Mr. Austin Okere has served as Non-Executive Vice Chairman of Computer Warehouse Group Plc since January 1, 2016. Until January 1, 2016, he served as Managing Director/Chief Executive Officer, Executive Director of the Company. Austin is a graduate of Computer Science from the University of Lagos. He also holds an MBA degree from Instituto de Estudios Superiores de la Empresa (IESE), Navara, Spain. He is a member of several professional and leadership bodies, including ICT Advisory Board, Nigerian Competitive Council and Nigerian Economic Summit Group. He also serves on the Executive Committee of the Nigerian-South African Chamber of Commerce. He has been recognized locally and internationally with many awards in recognition of his contribution to the information and communications technology world. He is currently an Entrepreneur in Residence at Columbia Business School, New York.




							Obianuju Ejeh-Nnabuife


					
							Mrs. Obianuju Ejeh-Nnabuife serves as Chief Financial Officer of Computer Warehouse Group Plc. She has enormous experience in the areas of audit, financial and risk advisory, financial control and treasury. She commenced her career at KPMG, where she provided audit and advisory services to banks, discount houses and insurance companies. She was one of the pioneer staff of the finance and treasury division at Africa Finance Corporation (AFC), the African-focused Development Financial Institute. She also worked in other sectors such as the Retail and Oil and Gas in both Nigeria and the Middle East. Mrs. Ejeh-Nnabuife holds a Masters of Business Administration degree from Manchester Business School, UK. She also has a Bachelors degree in Mathematics and Economics from the University of Benin. She is an associate Member of ICAN and a CFA Charter holder.




							Kunle Ayodeji


					
							Mr. Kunle Ayodeji has served as Chief Operating Officer, Executive Director of Computer Warehouse Group Plc since January 1, 2016. He served as Executive Director for Finance and Operations of the Company between April 16, 2015 and January 1, 2016. He served as Non-Executive Director of the Company until January 1, 2016. Kunle is an Associate Director with The Abraaj Group and has over 10 years' experience in the fields of banking, financial consulting and private equity. Prior to joining Abraaj in 2007, he was a Senior Consultant with the Financial Advisory Services unit of KPMG Nigeria where he was involved with the valuation, due diligence and feasibility studies for various corporations and state governments. He also worked at the Treasury Operations department of Triumphbank Plc in Lagos, Nigeria. He has been instrumental in the investment of over US$ 45 million of Abraaj Funds, two partial divestments and two full exit of Abraaj's portfolio companies in Nigeria. He currently sits on the board of a number of Abraaj's portfolio companies. Kunle holds a B.Sc. in Economics from Obafemi Awolowo University, Nigeria and an MBA from the University of Birmingham, United Kingdom.




							Folasade Afolabi-Modebelu


					
							Ms. Folasade Afolabi-Modebelu serves as General Counsel – Company Secretary of Computer Warehouse Group Plc. Folasade started her career 16 years ago at the Legal Services Commission, UK where she gained vast experience in regulatory and contract compliance. Her experience cuts across Commercial and Corporate Practice, Corporate Governance, Foreign investments, Telecoms Law and Aviation having worked both as in-house counsel and lawyer in the public and private sector. Whilst at Abraham and Co, she was Head of Corporate Governance and managed the company secretarial section. She has a proven track record of advising on diverse commercial transactions from negotiation to conclusion. Folasade has advised on a State government project relating to IT and Intellectual property law. She obtained her LL.B from Obafemi Awolowo University, Ile-Ife. She thereafter, obtained an LLM from Southampton University, U.K in 2000. She is a member of the Nigerian Bar Association and was admitted to the roll of Solicitors (England and Wales) in 2004.




							Harriet Yartey


					
							Ms. Harriet Attram Yartey serves as Managing Director, Ghana of Computer Warehouse Group Plc. She has over 15 years of diversified experience, which includes the 3-years she has been with CWG PLC. Harriet has been instrumental in building and scaling CWG Ghana’s businesses successfully. She is noted for her passion for excellence, customer centricity and precision in execution. She has been active in turning around the CWG Ghana business to achieve market leadership in the area of enterprise solutions and services, revenue growth and profitability. She has acquired experience in all the three areas of ICT – working with a number of premier ICT companies in Ghana. Prior to taking up the responsibility of managing the CWG Ghana operations, Harriet worked at Channel IT as the General Manager and before that she was with Vodafone Ghana. She holds Bachelor of Arts degree from University of Ghana and an Executive MBA from Ghana Institute of Management and Public Administration. She has also attended several trainings both local and offshore.




							Eniye Alile


					
							Ms. Eniye Alile serves as Head, Human Resources of Computer Warehouse Group Plc. She has over ten years’ experience providing Human Resources services to clients in diverse industries in Nigeria. Her areas of expertise include training, recruitment, employee welfare, performance management and implementation of employee recognition and incentive schemes. Eniye has a Bachelor of Science degree in Geography and Regional Planning from the University of Benin. She is also a member of the Institute of Chartered Accountant of Nigeria (ICAN). She is a certified Global Professional in Human Resources (GPHR) of the HR Certification Institute (HRCI), a Global Remuneration Professional (GRP) from the World-at-Work Society and an Associate from the Chartered Institute of Personnel Management of Nigeria (ACIPMN).




							Adewale Adeyipo


					
							Mr. Adewale Adeyipo serves as Director, Telecommunication Sector of Computer Warehouse Group Plc. He has over 12 years of experience in Consultative Sales and Managed Services Engagements For Telecommunication Companies. Adewale holds a BSc in Computer Science from University of Ilorin, he is an Alumni of Lagos Business School (LBS) and has also attended premium Sales and Leadership trainings both Locally and Internationally. Adewale worked at Discount Finance House in 2005, where he was responsible for providing Platforms and Mechanism to enhance the delivery of Micro Finance Credit Scheme both for government and private agencies. Thereafter, he worked with e-Peak Systems in 2007. Moreover, Adewale has held several leadership positions in CWG including business development for the Telecommunication arm in 2010 and Business Director for PAN Africa Initiatives in 2014. Due to his wide-spread experience, Adewale also doubles as the service director for CWG managed services team in MTNN, assuring the delivery of the company’s industry-leading cloud services and portfolio of outsourced IT services, while also creating similar opportunities with other telecoms.




							Bola Adisa


					
							Mr. Bola Adisa serves as FSI Sector Director of Computer Warehouse Group Plc. Bola Adisa is a versatile and experienced professional, with demonstrated exceptional abilities in technology, business and process management during the course of his career. He has keen interests in research, business analysis, and IT business solutions and systems development. With over 15 years of professional experience in the ICT sector, Bola had at various times in his career functioned as Field/Network Engineer, Sales Support Specialist (Pre-sales), Business Requirement Analyst, Business Development Manager, and Business Solutions Manager with key IT companies both indigenous and multi-nationals in Nigeria. Bola had undergone various IT Trainings in VSAT and Networking Solutions and also in leading business application software like SAP, Oracle, etc. He does have knowledge of Business Systems to address Industry specific challenges. Bola is certified SAP Business Process Consultant. His business systems experience cuts across different industries having been part of turnkey IT projects and business solutions in Banking, Oil & Gas, Manufacturing, Utilities and Telecoms Industries in different technical and business capacity. Bola had previously worked with organizations like KPS Limited, our own ExpertEdge Software & Systems Ltd, and Multinationals like SAP and International Data Corporation (IDC). Bola joined CWG from the IDC West Africa, a ICT Research and Consulting firm, where he was the Country Regional Manager leading the entire business operations and managing the resources to grow the West African business of IDC, with key focus on Business Development, General Management, Sales Strategy Development, P & L Management and is part of the Sub-Saharan Africa Management team.




							Udukheli Izebuno


					
							Mr. Udukheli Izebuno serves as Government Business Sector Director of Computer Warehouse Group Plc. Udukheli Izebuno is a multilingual, growth driven professional with over 12 years experience in telecoms, banking, consulting, import trade and retail finance. He has a proven record of work performance and experience in Team management, business expansion and development as well as new market penetration. He is a seasoned sales and business development professional with degrees in Accounting, Geography and Regional Planning from the University of Jos, Nigeria and Ambrose Alli University, Nigeria respectively. He started his career as a sales executive with multinational telecoms giant, Globacom Nigeria after which he served as pioneer Area Manager, GloMobile, Republic du Benin, Northern Borgu before joining Diamond Bank Plc as Pioneer Regional Sales Manager, Northern Nigeria. He further served as General Manager, LeezWorld Enterprise Ltd and was pivotal to the transformation of the large-scale enterprise to a flourishing process driven business. Prior to joining Computer Warehouse Group (CWG) in 2015 as a Regional Operations Manager-East, He was instrumental in taking One Credit Ltd, a leading Fintech company over the Billion Naira business mark serving as the company Head of sales and business development. He is now the Head of CWG Government Businesses focusing on public sector initiatives across the country.




							Rasheed Salawu


					
							Mr. Rasheed Salawu serves as Business Director, Emergent Business Group of Computer Warehouse Group Plc. He is a solution-driven professional with vast experience in banking, consulting, business development, project implementation, and support. He is a Project Management Professional with degrees in Computer Science and Business Administration. He started his career with Standard Trust Bank (now United Bank for Africa) before joining Computer Warehouse Group (CWG) in 2005 as an Information System consultant with specialization in banking solutions, implementation, and support. He has served in various capacities in CWG ranging from technical support, business development, project implementation, presales, and sales. He was the Program Manager for Expert Edge Software, a former division of Computer Warehouse Group Limited, the position he held until January 2012 when he was promoted as the Pioneer Group, Program Manager for Computer Warehouse Group to oversee portfolio project delivery. He was successful in institutionalizing project management culture in CWG. In September 2015, he was appointed as the Business Director CWG 2.0 to oversee the new business line of CWG targeted at growing platform business in line with the vision 2020 of the company. He is now the Head of Emergent Business Group focusing on Oil & Gas and Mining; Manufacturing and FMCG; Services, Logistics and Hospitality; SMEs & Retail; and Educational Sector.




							Daniel Shoban-Das


					
							Mr. Daniel Shoban-Das serves as Sector Head, Utility of Computer Warehouse Group Plc. Daniel Shoban-Das has extensive technological expertise in Embedded Electronics, Power Measurement Systems and High Bandwidth WiFi Mesh technologies. He also has an active interest in applying Artificial Intelligence Systems for Predictive Analysis in the financial markets. He founded his start-up Daniel Power Systems in 2009, in which he developed and commercialized smart solutions for the power distribution companies in India. Daniel is responsible for building the Utility business at Computer Warehouse Group, encompassing Water Utilities, Waste Management, Power Distribution and Broadband Services over WiFi.




							Philip Obioha


					
							Mr. Philip Obioha has served as Non-Executive Director of Computer Warehouse Group Plc since January 1, 2016. Until January 1, 2016, he served as Chief Operating Officer, Executive Director of the Company. Phillip Obioha is a consummate professional with a reputation for brokering and assuring the smooth conclusion of the most complicated negotiations and transactions. Philip trained as an Electrical Engineer at the West Virginia University, Morgantown, West Virginia in USA, however his mastery of financial engineering and operations raises the bar in the realm of business finance and operations. Phillip also holds an MBA from Instituto de Estudios Superiores de la Empresa (IESE), Navara, Spain, as well as several information technology product certifications. He is a member of several professional bodies including the Institute of Directors (IOD).




							Adedoyin Odunfa


					
							Mrs. Adedoyin Odunfa serves as Non-Executive Director of Computer Warehouse Group Plc. Adedoyin is an IT professional with over 20 years in professional practice, focused on enhancing the strategic value of IT in organizations through value-adding interventions across the Information Value Chain. Adedoyin has Spearheaded many broad-based initiatives with wide spread impact in IT Governance, Risk and Compliance across the public and private sectors of the economy. She is the founder and CEO of Digital Jewel Ltd, a leading professional service firm which is currently the only ISO27001 ( Information Security Management ) certified company in Africa which is also a Qualified Security Assessor (PCI DSS QSA) in Africa. Adedoyin s a recognized leader in the IT Industry and has the following credentials to her name Certified Information System Auditor (CISA), Certified Information System Security Professional (CISSP), certified in the Governance of Enterprise IT (CGEIT), Project management Professional (PMP), Certified Cobit 5 Implementer And Assessor. Adedoyin holds a B.sc (Combined Honors) in Computer Science and Economics from the Obafemi Awolowo University, Ile Ife and MBA (Information technology and Management) from the City University Business School (now Cass business School) in UK.




							Olusegun Oso


					
							Dr. Olusegun (Segun) Oso serves as Non-Executive Director of Computer Warehouse Group Plc. Dr. Olusegun Oso is a Non-Executive Director representing The Abraaj Group, a leading private equity investor in global growth markets. He is a seasoned professional with experience spanning various fields including healthcare delivery, investment banking and private equity. Segun is a member of Abraaj’s investment team in Sub-Saharan Africa where as Lead Health Specialist he focuses on initiatives aimed at increasing access to affordable and good quality healthcare for mid to low income populations in Africa. Prior to joining Abraaj in 2010, Segun was co-head of Investment Banking at Afrinvest West Africa where he advised on M & A and capital raising transactions in financial services, telecommunications and manufacturing. Segun attended the University of Ibadan where he earned a bachelor’s degree in Medicine and Surgery (MBBS). He also holds an MBA degree from the Sloan School of Management at the Massachusetts Institute of Technology, USA.











